From: Limeng <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 18 May 2016 16:02:21 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] driver: usb: dwc2: add delay for enumerating usb device
 successfully

When plug in an usb device(usb disk), host fail to enumerate it.
Because usb controller needs a period of time to restore from
suspend status, and then works normally. Therefore, add delay
time to wait for controller to correctly update D+/D- level and
detect port connect so that enumerate successfully.
This fix refer to mainline upstream commit 5634e016cf6e

Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c |    6 ++++++
 1 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c b/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
index 2b42851..e9b70fb 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
@@ -2326,6 +2326,12 @@ static int _dwc2_hcd_resume(struct usb_hcd *hcd)
 	struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg = dwc2_hcd_to_hsotg(hcd);
 
 	hsotg->lx_state = DWC2_L0;
+
+	/* Wait for controller to correctly update D+/D- level
+	 * and detect Port Connect
+	 */
+	usleep_range(12000, 14000);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
